{"type":"text","timestamp":1784658797389,"sessionID":"ses_07a0c8466ffeMf5yrsVMMSY7jO","part":{"id":"prt_f85f41b790018yD6sc3Gg3Me8o","messageID":"msg_f85f418e4001tzts6OCbrmRnbj","sessionID":"ses_07a0c8466ffeMf5yrsVMMSY7jO","type":"text","text":"Implemented a full project scaffold for **EchoPlex**:\n\n### Backend (`/backend`)\n- **`requirements.txt`** – FastAPI, Uvicorn, PostgreSQL, Neo4j, spaCy, Transformers, Dask, etc.\n- **`main.py`** – FastAPI app with health check, placeholder ingestion and pattern endpoints, Pydantic models.\n- **`Dockerfile`** – Multi‑stage image building the Python environment and exposing port 8000.\n\n### Frontend (`/frontend`)\n- **`package.json`**, **`vite.config.js`**, **`Dockerfile`** – Vite‑based React 18 setup with Auth0, Vega‑Lite, and React‑Vega.\n- **`src/App.jsx`** – Basic UI with Auth0 login/logout and a sample Vega‑Lite timeline.\n- **`src/main.jsx`** – Root entry point wiring Auth0 provider.\n- **`index.html`** – Simple HTML host.\n\n### Project Infrastructure\n- **`.gitignore`** – Ignores Python caches, Node modules, build artifacts, OS files.\n- **`docker-compose.yml`** – Orchestrates PostgreSQL, Neo4j, backend, and frontend services with environment placeholders for Auth0 credentials.\n- Updated **`README.md`** already contains the project description.\n\nThe repository now contains a runnable Docker‑Compose setup that launches the database services, a FastAPI backend ready for further ingestion/pattern logic, and a React frontend ready for UI development and authentication integration. You can start the stack with:\n\n```bash\ndocker compose up --build\n```\n\nFrom there, expand the backend routes, add ML/NLP pipelines, and flesh out the UI visualizations as needed.","time":{"start":1784658795385,"end":1784658797385}}}
